snippet: Gerald Green scored 23 points, and Kris Humphries had 18 points and 13 rebounds as the Nets beat Philadelphia, dealing a serious blow to the Sixers’ Eastern Conference push.
abstract: NBA Roundup; New Jersey Nets beat Philadelphia 76ers, 95-89; other NBA results noted.
lead_paragraph: Gerald Green scored 23 points, and Kris Humphries had 18 points and 13 rebounds as the Nets beat Philadelphia, dealing a serious blow to the Sixers’ Eastern Conference push.
